      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">In a system where the units work in parallel,
the parallel communication shares the operation mode of each unit
with the other units. The behavior of a redundant system will be different
depending on if the system have individual batteries or a common battery.</p>
            <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">Depending on parameter settings for your specific
system design, the tables might not show all system behaviors or your
system might behave differently in a certain situation.</note>
            <note class="- topic/note ">The shown behaviors assume that boost charge is not inhibited.</note>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
